{#ivASramadrumezu#} <ls>Ś. 1. 32</ls>; <ls>Me. 105</ls>; <ls>Bk. 7. 9</ls>,
<ls n="Pt.">21. 6.</ls>

{@--2@} To fly, move through
the air, soar; {#haMtuM kalahakAro'sO#} 
{#SabdakAraH papAta KaM#} <ls>Bk. 5. 100</ls>; see {#patat#}
below.

{@--3@} To set, sink (below the
horizon); {#soyaM caMdraH patati#} 
{#gaganAdalpaSezErmayUKE#} <ls>Ś. 4</ls> <ab>v. l.</ab>;  
{#patatpataMgapratimastaponiDiH#} <ls>Śi. 1. 12.</ls>

{@--5@} To fall (in
a moral sense), lose one's caste, 

forfeit one's rank or position, fall off:
{#paraDarmeRa jIvan hi sadyaH patati jAtita#};
<ls>Ms. 10. 97</ls>, <ls n="Ms.">3. 16</ls>, <ls n="Ms.">5. 19</ls>, <ls n="Ms.">9. 200</ls>;  
<ls>Y. 1. 38.</ls>

{@--6@} To come down (as from
heaven); {#pataMti pitaro hyezAM#} 
{#luptapiMqodakakriyAH#} <ls>Bg. 1. 42.</ls>

{@--7@} To fall, be
reduced to wretchedness or misery;
{#prAyaH kaMdukapAtenotpatatyAryaH patannapi#}  
<ls>Bh. 2. 123.</ls>

{@--8@} To go down into hell,
go to perdition; <ls>Ms. 11. 37</ls>;  
<ls>Bg. 16. 16.</ls>

{@--9@} To fall, occur, come to
pass, take place; {#lakzmIryatra pataMti tatra#}
{#vivftadvArA iva vyApadaH#} <ls>Subhāṣ.</ls>

{@--10@}
